{
    "analysis": "From the previous Executor output: metric.csv contains many component-KPI groups (top 50 shown) with full-series statistics (count, min, max, mean, median, P90, P95, P99). The metric timestamps in the file span 2024-01-19 22:28:00+00:00 to 2024-01-19 22:52:00+00:00, which lies inside the incident window (2024-01-19 22:25:08 to 2024-01-19 22:55:08 UTC) so we have metric coverage for the incident. trace.csv appears empty (no trace telemetry present). log.csv contains two log_name keys: log.error_count and log.row_count with 229 rows total, implying log telemetry exists and should be inspected next. Since traces are not available, we'll rely primarily on metrics and logs. The next step is to perform anomaly detection on metric KPIs using global thresholds (calculated from full-series per component-KPI) and then inspect metrics within the incident window to find faults.",
